- intro:
    - long lines at conferences, temperature too hot, not enough food
    - other complaints
    - praises, things doing well
    
- how our app works:
    - pulls twitter feed
    - tags it using the cortana analytics whether happy or sad
    - displays it split between 2 lists
    
- what our app uses
    - twitter api
    - redis backend storage
    - Cortana analytics:
        - the text analytics APIs: read the tweets and score it: happy vs sad
        - Emotion API: The emotions detected are anger, contempt, disgust, fear, happiness, neutral, sadness, and surprise.

-how does this help?
    - able to get instafeedback on conferences
    - provides for better conference experience
    